THE rotten smell of a body hung in the house and flies could be heard buzzing.And when the cops finally arrived, residents couldn&rsquo;t believe that the gogo had been sleeping next to her husband&rsquo;s corpse for four days. It happened in Bophelong, Vaal.The gogo said she didn&rsquo;t suspect anything when her husband didn&rsquo;t eat and wake up, and she went on with her days as normal.She said after two days she was shocked when she realised she had been sleeping next to a corpse, but that she panicked and didn&rsquo;t know what to do.&ldquo;When I saw my husband&rsquo;s body was starting to rot, I fetched his relative,&rdquo; she told Daily Sun.Police spokeswoman Sergeant Gertrude Makhale said the body had no visible injuries. &ldquo;A post mortem will determine the cause of death,&rdquo; she said.Makhale said an inquest docket was opened at Vanderbijlpark Police Station.